              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1131783-eddie-watkins?shelf=uk-fiction">uk-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer45637093" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9151130170384833597">One of the great hermetic works of literature. A complete and total world unto itself, almost to the point of detaching from the Earth and assuming its own orbit. If it were to do this it would be a strangely barren world however, a barren world of endlessly ramifying imagination, an almost airless world, a world both vast and microscopic. These books, this world, induced a tremendous sense of mental claustrophobia in this reader, yet all these years later I still long to return to it.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


